        h1 Maison<br>Apothecare
        .caption &mdash; Branding, Packaging, Art Direction
    
    section.copy
      blockquote 
        i Maison Apothecare
        |  is a growing maker of exquisite, small batch products made using
        |  100% pure plant derived extracts.
      hr
      p Working with
        i  Maison Apothecare
        | , I designed the brand and packaging which helped to strongly establish
        |  their place in the local beauty care market in Canada.
      p Growing from a small wholesale business, 
        i  Maison Apothecare
        |  (originally
        i  Modern Apothecary
        | ) now sells to department and grocery stores, and has opened three
        |  brick-and-mortar shops and an affiliate shop in the UK.
      
    img(src="/images/ma-1.png")

    section.copy
      h1 Branding
      h2 Logo
      p Originally called 
        i  Modern Apothecary
        | , the name called for a logo that blended modernness with
        |  the feeling of an antique apothecary. The mix of antique
        |  calligraphic lines with a modern font clearly articulates
        |  the intended brand image.

      img(src="/images/maisonapothecare-1.png")
      h2 Shape
      p The 
        i  Maison Apothecare
        |  label shape was designed to reflect and complement the shape and
        |  antique quality of the logo design. The recognizable and unique
        |  label shape is used across the signature product line.
      
      img(src="/images/maisonapothecare-4.png")
      hr.spacer
      h2 Colour
      p The bright modern colour palette was designed to reflect the 
        |  upbeat, family-oriented nature of the brand, while also
        |  representing the product scents in a familiar way.

